  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing Competitiveness and Market Orientation of Innovation-Driven Goat Processing Value Chains in the Republic of Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In early 2019, UNIDO and the Government of Zambia initiated the formulation of the new PCP programme. UNIDO conducted several missions to the country to discuss the PCP with government counterparts and development partners, and facilitate the transition from the ongoing UNIDO Country Programme into a PCP. The main focus areas are identified as (i) Improving the policy environment; (ii) Industrial skills development; and (iii) Fostering manufacturing industries and value addition in primary commodities. This project aims to address supply-side constraints and market access inadequacies focusing on the priorities identified in the DTIS Action Matrix, such as improving competitiveness as well as quality and standards of local agricultural/livestock products both in domestic and international markets resulting in enhanced efficiency and expanded socio-economic impact of the goat processing value chain in Zambia.  UNIDO has developed, tested and refined globally a set of tools that it uses to support its programmes for the promotion of the agro-industrial sector. Specifically, UNIDO#s experience in implementing the project #Promoting sustainable bush-processing value chains# in the region possesses significant technical assistance potential from which goat processing value chains in Zambia could benefit. The UNIDO p</narrative>
  </description>
